{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐξετ-άζω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> ἐξετάσω, rarely ἐξετῶ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 9.34, compare “Anecdota Graeca - Bekker” 251\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐξήτασα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 438, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 211 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc., <i>Doric dialect</i> ἐξήταξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 14.28 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἐξήτακα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 154d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> <b>-ετασθήσομαι</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.20: \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> -ητάσθην (see. below): <i>perfect</i> -ήτασμαι (see. entry near the end):—<b>examine well</b> or <b>closely, scrutinize, review,</b> ἐ. φίλους, ὅντιν᾽ ἔχουσι νόον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1016, cf. Ar.[same place], etc.; τὴν ὑπάρχουσαν ξυμμαχίαν ἐ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.7; βίον αὐτοῦ πάντα ἐξετάσω 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.21; ἐκ τοῦ εἰκότος ἐξετασθῆναι δεῖ τὸ πρᾶγμα 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.37 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ., opposed to ὑπέχειν λόγον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1354a5 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ δι᾽ ἀκριβείας -αζόμενον exactly <b>weighed</b> words, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 184c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. τι [διὰ] τῶν εἰδότων <b>make inquiries into</b> a thing <b>from..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.8.1: followed by Relat., ἐ. ὅστις ἦν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 45.82; ἐ. τί καὶ πῶς λέγουσι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 261a; ἐ. τινά, τίνος ἐστὶ γένους 4th c.BC: Epicrates Comicus 11.17. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of troops, <b>inspect, review,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.33, 35, etc.; στρατιώτας σὺν τοῖς ὅπλοις “Hellenica Oxyrhynchia” 10.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, στρατὸς δὲ θάσσει κἀξετάζεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 391, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.97. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> ἐ. τὴν βουλήν, τὸ βουλευτικόν, = Latin <i>legere senatum</i>, <b>revise the roll of</b> the Senate, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 52.42, 54.13. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>examine, approve,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PRev.Laws 40.19 (_passive_, 3rd c.BC), etc. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>pass in review, enumerate,</b> ἁμαρτήματα ἀκριβῶς ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7.63, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.52,58. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>examine</b> or <b>question</b> a person <b>closely,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.62, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 586, “OC” 211; τινὰ περί τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 258d; τινά τι [prev. author] “Grg.” 515b, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.2.35; δικαίως αὐτὸν ἐξετάσω 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.154, compare 18.20; τὸν δεσπότην ὁ δοῦλος ἐξετάζει [prev. author] 45.76 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 65. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>estimate,</b> τι πρός τι one thing with reference to another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 6.7; πρὸς ἐκείνους ἐ. καὶ παραβάλλειν ἐμέ [prev. author] 18.314; ἰσοστάσιος ἦν ἡ πορφύρα πρὸς ἄργυρον ἐξεταζομένη 4th c.BC: Theopompus Historicus 114, compare 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 3.119a; ἐ. τινὰ παρ᾽ ἄλληλα 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.265, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>compare,</b> πρὸς Ἀριστογείτονα ἐμαυτόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator “Epistulae” 3.43. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>prove by scrutiny</b> or <b>test,</b> of gold, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Chilo Lyricus 1 (_passive_)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. τοὺς κακούς τε κἀγαθούς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 20.14; τοὺς χρησίμους 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 34.38 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, ἐξητακὼς στερεοὺς ὑπάρχοντας τοὺς τόπους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.79.1:\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] —more frequently in <i>passive</i>, ἐὰν μὴ παρὼν ἐ. unless he is <b>proved</b> to have been present, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 764a; καὶ λέγων καὶ γράφων ἐξηταζόμην τὰ δέοντα 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.173; ἐξήτασαι πεποιηκώς [prev. work]197; ἐξετάζεσθαι φίλος (i.e. ὤν) 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 1011; ἐχθρὸς ἐξεταζόμενος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.65; κατήγορος [prev. author] 22.66; μέτριοι ἐν τοῖς ἀνηκέστοις 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.74b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of things, τὰ φοβερὰ ἐξετασθήσεται μέχρι λόγου τοιαῦτα ὄντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.63. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be numbered, counted,</b> with <i>genitive</i>, ὧν εἷς ἐγὼ βουληθεὶς ἐξετάζεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.2; τῶν ἐχθρῶν εἷς ἐξετάζεσθαι \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>to be found in the number of..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.291 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μετὰ τῶν ἄλλων ἐξητάζετο he <b>appeared among..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 18.217; ἔν τισι 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.59 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be placed on a roll,</b> ἐν τοῖς ἱππικοῖς among the [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Equites” at Rome, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 14 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of the census, ἐξητάσθησαν αἱ πᾶσαι πεντεκαίδεκα [μυριάδες] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. author]\">Refs</a>]<b>caes.</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 55. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__V.2</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, <b>present oneself, appear,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.161; πρὸς τὸν ἄρχοντα.. οὐδέπω.. ἐξήτασται [prev. author] 37.46, compare 18.277. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1833","accentedUnicode":"ἐξετάζω","shortDef":"to make a search; to ask, inquire, question find out","mediumDef":"to make a search; to ask, inquire, question find out <br /><b>to search out; to inquire by interrogation, examine strictly,</b> <ref='Mat.2.8; 10:11'>Mt. 2:8; 10:11</ref>; <b>to interrogate,</b> <ref='Jhn.21.12'>Jn. 21:12</ref>*","stepGloss":"to find out","stepTransliteration":"exetazō","count":3,"_es_Definition":"buscar ; hacer una búsqueda meticulosa ; preguntar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 檢驗, 查詢, 細查 (太 2:8, 10:11)<br>2) 質問, 檢驗 (約 21:12)","_zh_Definition":"1) 检验, 查询, 细查 (太 2:8, 10:11)<br>2) 质问, 检验 (约 21:12)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"tìm hỏi. ἐκ (G1537) + ἐτάζω (xem xét)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要打聽","_es_Gloss":"averiguar  ","_zh_Gloss":"要打听"}]}